technologies.name: TypeScript
technologies.description: TypeScript is an open-source language which builds on JavaScript  by adding static type definitions.

technologies.name: TinyMCE
technologies.description: TinyMCE is an online rich-text editor released as open-source software. TinyMCE is designed to integrate with JavaScript libraries, Vue.js, and AngularJS as well as content management systems such as Joomla!, and WordPress.

technologies.name: ApexCharts.js
technologies.description: ApexCharts is a modern JavaScript charting library that empowers developers to build interactive data visualizations for commercial and non-commercial projects.

technologies.name: Angular
technologies.description: Angular is a TypeScript-based open-source web application framework led by the Angular Team at Google.

technologies.name: Nginx
technologies.description: Nginx is a web server that can also be used as a reverse proxy, load balancer, mail proxy and HTTP cache.

technologies.name: Google Font API
technologies.description: Google Font API is a web service that supports open-source font files that can be used on your web designs.

technologies.name: HSTS
technologies.description: HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) informs browsers that the site should only be accessed using HTTPS.

technologies.name: Webpack
technologies.description: Webpack is an open-source JavaScript module bundler.

technologies.name: PWA
technologies.description: Progressive Web Apps (PWAs) are web apps built and enhanced with modern APIs to deliver enhanced capabilities, reliability, and installability while reaching anyone, anywhere, on any device, all with a single codebase.

technologies.name: Module Federation
technologies.description: Module Federation is a webpack technology for dynamically loading parts of other independently deployed builds.
